section.section:
The Commissioner may place an inmate in a center operated by Cecil County if the inmate:
has been committed by the court to the custody of the Commissioner;
is a legal resident of Cecil County;
has:
less than 6 months remaining on a sentence;
less than 6 months remaining until a determined parole date; or
a sentence of 3 years or less; and
has been screened by a center staff member and approved by the center director in accordance with subsection (b) of this section.
